observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

a.  Require the HRMO – Designate to ensure regular posting of all vacant positions in accordance with CSC regulations;

b. Evaluate the agency’s current organizational structure, reassess and make manning proposals ensuring that qualifications standards are observed; if needed, realign the qualified  employees to a higher position matching their qualifications to the qualification standards, and that their respective position matches the requirements / demands of their  designations / assigned functions;

c.  Consider filling up the vacant positions through promotion of qualified regular personnel thereby allowing entry of new applicants for lower-level positions; and

d.  Give priority to existing contract of service or job orders in filling up the vacancies subject to the same qualification  standards required in each position.

We recommended that Management require the Accountant to:

a.Submit to COA the demand letters claimed to have been issued to and duly received by concerned officers and employees, otherwise, if not available, issue new demand letter/s thereto for the immediate liquidation of their outstanding cash advances, copy furnished the COA Auditor;

b)Withhold the salaries in satisfaction thereof for those failing to liquidate after due notice, or if not feasible, apply more stringent methods of collection, such as the institution of legal action against the person/s accountable; 

c.Demand the immediate submission of the duly approved report of disbursements and report of checks issued and/or refund from the implementing NGAs and other LGUs for the unliquidated fund transfers;

d.Monitor closely the liquidation of cash advances and fund transfers within the above-cited reglementary period in order to avoid accumulation thereof; and

e. Refrain from granting additional cash advance to officers and employees unless their previous cash advance/s had been fully settled.

We recommended that Management: 

1. Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare and submit to the Municipal Accountant the Certified List of Taxpayers showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year, the amount of which shall be computed based on the Taxpayers’ Index prepared by the Municipal Assessor and the outstanding balances from the prior year’s receivables;

2. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
a) Refer to the above certified list as basis in the preparation of journal entry to set-up the RPT and SET receivables for the year and the corresponding Deferred RPT/SET Income;

b) Review the discrepancy between the RPT and SET receivables and take up necessary adjustments thereon;

3.Formulate strategies in intensifying tax collection such as but not limited to:
a) In order to determine the actual owner and beneficial users of the real properties:
a.1) Strengthen the linkages with other officials and agencies such as the Register of Deeds and real estate dealers who are sources of property
transaction information;
a.2) Seek assistance from the Barangay officials and employees.
b) Coordinate with the Provincial Treasurer’s Office with regard to the enforcement of administrative and judicial remedies as provided in the LGC; and
c) Employ other methods to encourage the payment of tax delinquencies.

